\begin{abstract}
 The rate and the complexity of the financial world development are such that real-time sentiment analysis of the news is becoming a more and more important tool in the hands of investors and analysts to make prudent decisions. The paper proposes a complete end-to-end system that is to be developed that can process financial news events in real-time with Kafka, Spark and Redis with the new state-of-art services of natural language processing. The latest news is delivered in our pipeline, all articles are categorized and enriched with the help of a rule-based approach and artificial intelligence models, and then finally made available to be analyzed immediately. It was tested to be able to process the large volumes without any issue and to perform on the new sources as well as the old ones and provide timely reliable results. We describe in the last point how automatic news sentiment can be useful in informing better finance decisions thereby moving to a future of truly data directed markets.
Index Terms— Real-time analytics on financial news with sentiment analysis, Big Data Systems, Apache Kafka, Apache Spark, NLP Redis Elasticsearch system

\end{abstract}

