\subsection{Data Flow and ETL Pipeline}

The pipeline is structured around a multi-step ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) process:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textit{Extraction:} The news articles are extracted and parsed Dedu- plication is performed by creating unique hashes from title, description and metadata combination.

\item \textit{Category Classification:} 
Articles are classified into 14 financial news categories using a hybrid weighted scoring method that combines DistilBART zero-shot transformer predictions with Redis-based keyword matching:
    \[
    C_{\text{score}}(\text{cat}) = \alpha \, C_{\text{AI}}(\text{cat}) + (1-\alpha) \, C_{\text{rules}}(\text{cat})
    \]
    where \( C_{\text{AI}}(\text{cat}) \) is the transformer score, \( C_{\text{rules}}(\text{cat}) \) is the keyword score, and \( \alpha = 0.7 \). The final category is selected via \( \arg\max_{\text{cat}} C_{\text{score}}(\text{cat}) \), combining semantic understanding with rule-based interpretability for efficient real-time classification.ng computational efficiency suitable for real-time streaming applications.

   \item \textit{Enrichment:} The Transform stage computes risk scores via keyword 
matching, normalizes confidence values, and derives impact metrics from pre-computed 
sentiment. The final score uses confidence-weighted balancing:
    \[
    S_{\text{final}} = I_{\text{score}} \cdot c_{\text{norm}} - R_{\text{raw}} \cdot (1 - c_{\text{norm}})
    \]
    where \( I_{\text{score}} \) is the impact score, \( R_{\text{raw}} \) is the 
    risk score, and \( c_{\text{norm}} \) balances their contributions based on 
    classification confidence.

    \item \textit{Storage and Visualization:} The enriched data along with all the computed metrics, categories and tickers is stored in Elasticsearch for efficient faceted search and interactive dashboard analytics.
\end{enumerate}


