\subsection{Fault Tolerance and Reliability}

Robustness is inherent in every process in the pipeline. If one of the downstream services fails (e.g. Elasticsearch or Redis), data batches are cached locally or queued and re-tried automatically. Rule-based classification offers a fallback in case of failure of AI models. Errors are logged, monitored and the backlogged data is processed, once the dependencies are restored.


\subsection{Innovations and Strengths}

This architecture is a combination of distributed event-driven processing with a new dual mode of categorization and sentiment classification - a combination of AI and rule-based scoring to increase both transparency and robustness. It has fall back mechanisms, confidence-weighted scoring, and real-time enrichment, which often is missing in traditional streaming analytics platforms.


\section{Algorithm 1: Financial News Sentiment Processing}

Input: Continuous stream of financial news articles from MarketAux API

Output: Enriched financial news records containing sentiment score, risk score, and impact score stored in Elasticsearch and visualized on dashboards.

1. Initialize system components  
Start Apache Kafka streaming service, start Apache Spark processing engine, initialize Redis keyword scoring database, and initialize Elasticsearch storage system.

2. Data Extraction  
Connect to the MarketAux financial news API and fetch the latest news articles $A_i$.

3. Data Preprocessing  
For each article $A_i$, extract title, description, timestamp, and source, remove HTML tags and unwanted characters, and normalize and tokenize the text.

4. Duplicate Detection  
Generate a unique hash $H_i$ from article metadata and discard the article if $H_i$ already exists, otherwise continue processing.

5. Hybrid Sentiment Analysis  
Collect sentiment scores from the MarketAux API and FinBERT model and combine them using confidence weighting with keyword overrides for polarity.

\begin{equation}
S_{final}=\frac{S_m \times C_m + S_f \times C_f}{C_m + C_f}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
C_{final}=\min(C_m + C_f,1.0)
\end{equation}

6. Hybrid Category Classification  
Perform DistilBART zero-shot classification on predefined financial categories and combine Redis keyword scoring with the model prediction to finalize the category.

\begin{equation}
Score_c = \alpha \times M_c + \beta \times K_c
\end{equation}

7. Text Enrichment using Language Model  
Generate article key phrases and summaries using DeepSeek-R1 and apply LangChain prompts for structured entity-focused summary generation.

8. Data Streaming  
Store the enriched article record in local archive storage and publish the processed article data to the Kafka topic Financenews-raw.

9. Stream Processing and Risk Evaluation  
Spark Structured Streaming consumes articles from the Kafka topic and evaluates contextual risk using sentiment, keywords, and confidence.

10. Impact and Final Score Calculation  
Assign impact labels based on sentiment polarity and risk level and compute the final score using impact score, confidence, and risk.

11. Data Storage  
Store enriched records in the Elasticsearch index.

12. API Access  
The Node.js backend retrieves analytics results and provides REST APIs for querying sentiment data.

13. Visualization  
The React dashboard displays sentiment trends, company-specific analytics, and news category distribution.

