\subsection{Hybrid Classification: Redis + Transformer Models}

One basic experiment used a weighted hybrid classification strategy in order to enhance label accuracy. Redis). stored sets of category-specific keywords for fast rule-based scoring whist the DistilBART transformer model performed contextual inference. The final score was calculated as follows:
\begin{equation}
C_{final} = \lambda \cdot C_{redis} + (1-\lambda) \cdot C_{transformer}
\end{equation}
where Cfinal is the combined prediction, Credis is the keyword-based score, Ctransformer is the transformer output, and λ controls the contribution of each component. This hybrid approach achieved 86–90 accuracy in test deployments and significantly reduced inference time, with Redis efficiently processing high-frequency batches. The workflow for this design is shown in  Figure~\ref{fig:hybrid_classification}.

