\subsection{ Pipeline Latency and Analytics Performance}

End-to-end pipeline latency - from raw ingestion of news to visualization on a dashboard were measured through integrated health endpoints and metrics endpoints. Median latency was < 4sec/art with throughput up to 1000 articles/hour in periods of stability. Sentiment trend graphs, card-based presentation of news, and per-ticker analytics were implemented in real time with frontend implementation of React +Vite/Recharts with filter and aggregation operations for the interactive performance.

\subsection{Summary of Results}

These experiments have shown that containerized orchestration using hybrid scoring and modular integration of AI produces a data pipeline that has good accuracy, low latency, and production-ready robustness. The system had a 99.7 uptime and constant analytic throughput, which validated the proposed design and its suitability for low-resource or agile setups. Moreover, about 90 of all processed outputs were released as structured documents of the open-source application with the "JSON" format that were then rendered via frontend UI for real-time analytical visualization, as shown in  Figure~\ref{fig:json_output}.

