\section{Conclusion}

This paper introduced a scalable, modular pipeline for real-time sentiment analysis of financial news based on the use of hybrid artificial intelligence models, rule-based logic and containerized big data systems. Experiments proved the combination of pretrained models and heuristics of Redis is better to classify, while Docker orchestration is used to guarantee reliable deployment on constrained hardware. With real-time monitoring and analytics, the architecture is good for practical financial applications.
For future work, more explorations including exploring continual learning in large language models, expanding to multilingual news streams, as well 1 further integrating explainable AI method- ologies are recommended. Additional research in the form of real-time feedback as well as human-in-the-loop pipelines can improve interpretability and trust for decision-makers. The approach outlined in this paper offers a basis for developing more intelligent, adaptive and transparent financial analytics systems in a rapidly changing data environment.



